The paper proposes a novel approach for transfer learning in brain-computer interfaces (BCIs) using electroencephalogram (EEG) data. The approach involves aligning covariance matrices in a Riemannian manifold, extracting features in the tangent space, and performing domain adaptation. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with neural networks and brain signals, which could place it in the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. The paper also involves image processing and feature extraction, which could place it in the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with data analysis and classification, which could place it in the statistical learning (cs.SD) sub-category.
